{
  "texts": [
    "The WaRP dataset was published in 2023 becoming the new benchmark dataset for both waste classification and detection task with 28 classes of waste materials.",
    "Our proposed classification (CL) model and object detection (DE) model (2S_DenseViT?",
    "GELAN-E) achieved a classification accuracy of 83.11%, and mAP of 0.63 significantly outperforming this study [42].During our test, we discovered that the 2S_DenseViT model performed inadequately in several trash categories, specifically the bottle-multicolor class.",
    "This performance gap is due to the visual complexity and unpredictability inherent in this class, which may impair the model's capacity to reliably discriminate these pictures.",
    "To solve this issue, future research will investigate sophisticated object detecting approaches."
  ]
}